<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="594" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[332,490,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Liocanthydrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mecespilus">
<emphasis box="[332,490,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">L. mecespilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other maculate species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1230,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Liocanthydrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1230,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Liocanthydrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: a) posterior and anterior bands of elytra very elongate (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1211,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 a – f" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[288,1312,198,1795]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[248,1327,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 a – f. Liocanthydrus mecespilus sp. nov. 2 a) dorsal habitus (scale = 1.0 mm); 2 b) median lobe of aedeagus, right lateral view; 2 c) idem, dorsal view; 2 d) idem, left lateral view; 2 e) left lateral lobe of aedeagus, right lateral view; 2 f) right lateral lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view (scale bar = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245886/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[1181,1197,727,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" value="2.0">2</number>
a
</figureCitation>
); b) posterior band extending nearly to apex from anterior half of elytron (
<figureCitation box="[797,882,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 a – f" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[288,1312,198,1795]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[248,1327,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 a – f. Liocanthydrus mecespilus sp. nov. 2 a) dorsal habitus (scale = 1.0 mm); 2 b) median lobe of aedeagus, right lateral view; 2 c) idem, dorsal view; 2 d) idem, left lateral view; 2 e) left lateral lobe of aedeagus, right lateral view; 2 f) right lateral lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view (scale bar = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245886/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[853,869,763,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" value="2.0">2</number>
a
</figureCitation>
); c) aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1176,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 a – f" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[288,1312,198,1795]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[248,1327,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 a – f. Liocanthydrus mecespilus sp. nov. 2 a) dorsal habitus (scale = 1.0 mm); 2 b) median lobe of aedeagus, right lateral view; 2 c) idem, dorsal view; 2 d) idem, left lateral view; 2 e) left lateral lobe of aedeagus, right lateral view; 2 f) right lateral lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view (scale bar = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245886/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
Figs 
<number box="[1121,1135,762,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" value="2.0">2</number>
b–f
</figureCitation>
), with distal region of median lobe sinuate in dorsal aspect, elongate and not parallel in lateral aspect, lateral flange enlarged; left lateral lobe with setal fringe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="594" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[353,515,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Measurements</emphasis>
(in mm). 
<typeStatus box="[632,736,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Holotype</typeStatus>
